content.$t: No longer under the original management, the 13th Note now has a vegetarian, although largely vegan menu.
No longer recommended! Previously listed as catering for vegan diets, but this is not the case. Now vegan un-friendly and staff unhelpful.
Used to be a Pacific Rim organic restaurant with good vegan options. Veggie choice diminished after change of management. Closed down in 2006
Standard neighbourhood Indian restaurant with above-average vegan service (thanks largely to once having a buddhist vegan chef). Vegan meals explicitly marked on the menu
Turkish restaurant with good veggie mezze selection
Excellent quality Greek Cypriot specialities, good vegetarian selection. N.B.falafel and keftedes are not vegan.
Large vegetarian selection in menu and a few vegan or veganizable
Hotel which has had occasional vegan nights in restaurant, and planned to have hot vegan breakfasts. Phone for current vegan support. See also Sutherlands Restaurant
Smart Scottish restaurant, vegan options available
No longer exclusively vegetarian, but still with vegan & vegetarian dishes. Family run. Vegetarian and non-vegetarian food prepared separately.

Omni outlet but with good range of Home-made vegan burgers & pakora. spinach & broccoli burgers especially recommended. Helpful and friendly owner. Open til 3.30am Thu, Fri, Sat. Also supply veggie burgers and pakora boxed for home or catering use (pakora popular for Glasgow weddings & christenings!). Previously known simply as the "Fast Food Bar"
South Indian takeaway with good range of vegan options, excellent dosas and so-so vadai
Several vegan options, e.g. bruschetta, panini, baked potatoes.
Belgian themed cafe bar. No regular vegan options although will prepare if booked in advance
Organic and fairly traded coffee, bread, juices and snacks. Clothing shop also has vegan shoes
Vegan options, large portions, and very helpful staff. Phone ahead for wider range of vegan choice, kitchen has a vegan guidance sheet available
Large selection of vegetarian with some vegan tapas
Large selection of vegetarian with some vegan tapas
Excellent small restaurant run by friendly and helpful husband and wife. Phone ahead for vegan options. Expensive but good value.
Good vegetarian selection and food cooked in oil rather than ghee
Veggie dishes appear limited to the indian menu
Chinese cash+carry, open to all. Cheap tofu, oriental fruit & veg.
Large vegetarian selection, enormous dosas and vegan-aware staff. Only sit-down South Indian restaurant in Glasgow, and at the other end of price scale from Banana Leaf takeaway
Greengrocery, bakery and deli, with vegan groceries, organics, snacks
Veganic farm offering workshops, courses and volunteerting. Campsite an caravan accomodation
Up a track (zoom out map to find)
Vegetarian and organic B&B, including organic/veggie bedding. All food vegetarian or vegan. Packed lunches and dinners also available.
Omnivorous B&B (also evening meals) catering for veggies and vegans. Handy for Glasgow & Prestwick airports.
Cafe with some vegan options, attached to an 'ethical' shop sells leather shoes and the usual hempware
Good Italian vegan staple - bruschetta, or ask for vegan pasta/pizza
Vegan take aways include hummous + crudites, baba ghannoush sandwiches and smoothies
Vegan starters, some pastas and pizzas can be made vegan. Intensely italian atmosphere. Service variable
Vegan / veggie breakfasts available on request
Huge choice of organic, vegan, japanese and italian products. Good magazine rack and wine choice. From 2009 also sell slaughter products
Vegetarian menu with regular vegan dishes. Vegan selection improving, and food generally excellent. Separate breakfast and snack menu. On site of old VegVille cafe. Closed as of March 2009
Co-operative based supplier of wholefoods to commercial premises and to individuals & food co-ops outside of Glasgow. All range is vegetarian and GM free.
Fruit and vegetables from the deli, plus some vegan options
Veggie dishes on offer and great vegan food on rquest
Pakistani / Indian greengrocers and shop. Good range of veggie ingredients in variety of bulk sizes, veggie frozen meals/snacks, pickles, spice mixes, canned goods
Vegan breakfasts, lunches and dinners by arrangement
Vegan and gluten free bakery. Supply Scottish classics such as Millionaire's Shortbread, biscuits and tray bakes to cafes, farmers markets and retailers.
Several vegan dishes and options always on the menu. Stylish & relaxed location with great reviews
Excellent Italian delicatessen, wineshop, cafe and pizzeria. Vegan panini and pasta
Tofu products, chinese fake meats, veg, noodles etc
Some dairy-free products including a freezer full of Swedish Glace choc ices. Reported as changed ownership late 2007
Organics and wholefood shop and home delivery

All vegan menu. Open until 1am. Breakfast, lunch, snack and dinner menus served all day. Wide range of organic and vegan drinks. Grocery shop now closed. Excellent record shop (Monorail) for vinyl, 2nd hand, eclectic and local bands
Good quality Indian restaurant, reasonable vegetarian selection, individually cooked dishes
Excellent food served in tapas style portions. Good veggie range. No table bookings and busy most nights
Regularly changing menu of soups, with 2 or 3 usually labelled both veggie and dairy-free.
New menu - vegan options now removed.
University cafe with Vegan Society certification, always vegan soup & main course available
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan yoghurts, bacon & cheeses. Occasionally vegan snacks and sandwiches
Vegan options, or ring ahead for better choice. Specialize in smaller dishes.
Produce vegetarian/vegan/diabetic cakes, dumplings, puddings and bread. Sell by mail order and via farmers markets
Russian owned and themed restaurant. Vegetarian and vegan options available on request
Now only occasionally sell vegan sandwiches and snacks. Soy lattes
Now only occasionally sell vegan sandwiches and snacks. Soy lattes
Now only occasionally sell vegan sandwiches and snacks. Soy lattes
Good range of vegan and organic products, fresh snacks and friendly service.
Offshoot of Shimla Pinks, offers cafe style Indian food, cheap curries, and vegan food on the menu
Local Italian run by two brothers from Rome. Veggie dishes on the menu and vegan dishes on request. Friendly helpful service
Vegan snacks, deli products, bread, ice cream

Huge chinese superstore and cash+carry, with wide range or oriental fruit, vegetable, frozen and dry goods. Cheap tofu blocks, large range of soy and seitan products. Large tanks of live lobsters & fish, and pigs heads at the back not for the squeamish
The usual good range of Lebanese mezze hot and cold
Cafe, and gift/clothes shop. Vegan options
Soup, baked potatoes and sandwiches. Always several veggie soups on menu and usually some of these are vegan. Staff are helpful, and all soups made on premises, so ingedients known.
Bakery and Bar. Vegan scones, cakes and more. Open from lunch til midnight. Regular touring bands.
Vegetarian and vegan breakfasts by prior arrangement
In Oct 09, had a separate entirely vegan a la carte menu, with several choices for starter, main and dessert. Restaurant for the Argyll Hotel.
Organic artisan bakery, café and coffee roasterie. Vegan options always available, and soy milk
Tea house, eclectic in its furniture and huge choice of teas. Soups are usually vegan, as can be the couscous and other dishes on request.
Unique hidden away tea house and garden, eclectic in its furniture and huge choice of teas. Soups are usually vegan, as can be the couscous and other dishes on request.
All vegan and largely organic menu served until 8pm. Good range of microbrews and organic beers, wine & ciders. Open peat fire, regular jazz nights, outside tables.
Used to be vegan, but now has meat main dishes. Claim veggie meals cooked separately in kitchen, and have good middle eastern dishes, vegan breakfasts, burgers and soy ice cream.
Nightclub themed as a tenement flat, with kitchen serving toast and tea (plus the usual bars)
Veggie+fish café with usually a choice of vegan dishes on the menu too, plus salads.
Deli with vegetarian menu entries and minimal vegan options (hummous and pitta)
Dairy-intensive veggie cafe with some vegan options. Food is locally sourced and organic where possible
Organic fruit and veg, vegan groceries, beauty products, children's clothes and jewellery
Japanese canteen style noodle restaurant. Small set of generous vegan selections always available on the menu, helpful staff knowledgable about vegan dishes
Japanese canteen style noodle restaurant. Small set of generous vegan selections always available on the menu, helpful staff knowledgable about vegan dishes
Tenement front-room sized offshoot of Mother India. Choice of 4 vegan dishes; food excellent and cheap. The original restaurant in a chain of 3
Individually cooked home style Indian food with good veggie selection
Individually cooked home style Indian food with good veggie selection. Opened at end of 2007, and maintains the cosy kitchen-centred feel of the original
Two of the pasties (vegetable and wholemeal vegetable) are now vegan - the new vegan ones have a yellow sticker on the box marked 'new glaze'
Some vegan sandwiches & smoothies, friendly staff will create if no vegan options left
Vegan breakfasts, packed lunches and dinners available on request
Sizable vegetarian menu, good variety of bean curd dishes.
Pakistani takeaway, with excellent cheap veggie curries (if you can overlook the variety of animal organs for sale)
